WEBVTT

00:03.236 --> 00:04.636
[Margaret groans]

00:04.638 --> 00:06.672
[sobbing]

00:06.674 --> 00:09.975
- [Millie] Every step's gonna make it easier, I promise.
- [Margaret moaning]

00:16.383 --> 00:19.685
<i>[woman 1] Somewhere in
me is this little glimmer of hope.</i>

00:19.687 --> 00:22.087
<i>I just wanna be a normal person.</i>

00:22.689 --> 00:25.657
[exhales sharply and pants]

00:33.099 --> 00:36.502
[man] You can't do it
and then I just get mad.

00:36.504 --> 00:39.605
<i>[woman 2] If I don't make a change
now, I'm scared it's gonna be too late.</i>

00:43.777 --> 00:46.979
No. [sobbing] It hurts!

00:46.981 --> 00:51.316
<i>[woman 3] I refuse to stop fighting.
I have to do this for my children.</i>

00:57.323 --> 01:00.692
I don't know what went wrong.
I don't know.

01:00.694 --> 01:03.996
You wanna argue all that
with the scale? Be my guest.

01:23.616 --> 01:30.089
<i>[Dr. Now] A couple hours ago, Margaret
and her mom showed up here at the hospital.</i>

01:30.091 --> 01:35.761
<i>Margaret apparently fell yesterday
and she went to emergency room.</i>

01:35.763 --> 01:40.099
<i>She was transferred to here
because they didn't have any facility</i>

01:40.101 --> 01:44.803
<i>that will take care of
somebody that is 750 pounds.</i>

01:44.805 --> 01:46.638
<i>She is 35 years old,</i>

01:47.340 --> 01:51.143
<i>and she managed
to become 750 pounds.</i>

01:52.212 --> 01:57.916
She is only 5 foot 4 inches
tall, and her BMI is 129,

01:57.918 --> 02:01.653
<i>which is one of the highest
BMI I have ever seen.</i>

02:01.655 --> 02:04.089
<i>And that is very dangerous BMI.</i>

02:04.091 --> 02:07.726
<i>That, combined with the fact
she is not mobile,</i>

02:07.728 --> 02:11.930
has created a very
dire situation for her.

02:11.932 --> 02:17.035
<i>And she can barely stand up
from her bed to bedside commode.</i>

02:17.804 --> 02:21.140
<i>When she fell,
she was short of breath.</i>

02:21.142 --> 02:26.145
<i>And she and her mom were
worried she was having a heart attack.</i>

02:26.147 --> 02:32.017
So we ran some tests on her to make sure
she doesn't have any life-threatening issues

02:32.019 --> 02:33.852
<i>we need to address right now.</i>

02:33.854 --> 02:38.657
But regardless, it's clear if
Margaret doesn't do something

02:38.659 --> 02:42.227
<i>to turn her life around, it's
only gonna be a matter of time</i>

02:42.229 --> 02:44.296
<i>before her body gives out.</i>

02:44.298 --> 02:49.034
<i>But at this point, I'm still
not sure she has any intention</i>

02:49.036 --> 02:51.336
to get the help
she needs to do that.

02:53.673 --> 02:54.706
Hello.

02:55.508 --> 02:56.441
[Margaret] Hello.

02:56.443 --> 02:58.977
Hi, Margaret.
I'm Dr. Nowzaradan.

02:58.979 --> 03:00.445
- [Margaret] Nice--
- How are you?

03:00.447 --> 03:02.147
Doing pretty good.
Nice to meet you.

03:02.149 --> 03:03.348
Nice to meet you.

03:04.317 --> 03:06.351
You weigh 750?

03:06.353 --> 03:07.986
[Margaret] Mm-hmm.

03:07.988 --> 03:10.122
So how long have you
been at that weight?

03:10.223 --> 03:11.857
I don't know.

03:11.859 --> 03:16.061
I haven't weighed myself
in three or four years.

03:16.063 --> 03:17.829
Do you get up and walk?

03:17.831 --> 03:21.233
The last time I was able to
really walk was six months ago.

03:21.235 --> 03:22.367
Who take care of you at home?

03:22.369 --> 03:23.902
My mom.

03:23.904 --> 03:28.140
Uh... so... Your mom
has any weight problem?

03:28.142 --> 03:30.642
She's had the gastric bypass.

03:30.644 --> 03:34.780
So if she had gastric bypass,
uh, why is she providing you

03:34.782 --> 03:37.683
too much food and keep you
in, uh, this way?

03:37.685 --> 03:40.452
Because it's easier
not to fight with me

03:41.154 --> 03:42.354
and just pacify me.

03:43.356 --> 03:47.226
So if she doesn't bring it
to you, what happen?

03:47.228 --> 03:49.461
I get mad at her and I tell
her that she doesn't love me.

03:50.096 --> 03:51.496
Okay.

03:51.931 --> 03:55.968
And so what do you think is gonna
happen to you if you continue that?

03:55.970 --> 03:57.369
I'm gonna die.

03:58.972 --> 04:02.007
I don't wanna die.
I wanna change.

04:02.009 --> 04:06.478
So why haven't you done anything to
change your situation up to this point?

04:08.281 --> 04:09.448
I've had abusive...

04:10.083 --> 04:11.416
Abusive life.

04:13.419 --> 04:17.656
What do you mean abusive? By
your parents? Or your family or who?

04:18.391 --> 04:21.293
My family. Especially my dad.

04:23.229 --> 04:24.463
I see.

04:24.465 --> 04:26.298
So you ate to deal with that.

04:26.300 --> 04:27.266
Yes.

04:27.268 --> 04:30.736
Food's my comfort.
I can hide underneath it.

04:30.738 --> 04:33.305
And nobody knows
what's going on in my life.

04:34.207 --> 04:37.142
So how motivated are you
to change your life

04:37.144 --> 04:42.481
and do your part and be able
to lose some weight?

04:42.483 --> 04:45.150
I'm willing to do
whatever I have to

04:45.152 --> 04:46.451
to have my surgery.

04:47.387 --> 04:48.920
All right.

04:48.922 --> 04:53.125
Okay, let's check a couple
thing and see how things are.

04:55.395 --> 04:58.997
I think we're gonna have our
work cut out for us with Margaret.

04:58.999 --> 05:02.901
<i>She says she wants
to change her situation,</i>

05:02.903 --> 05:06.338
<i>but so far she hasn't done
anything to change her life.</i>

05:06.340 --> 05:09.975
Can you lift your foot
up and down?

05:09.977 --> 05:15.647
Margaret said that she ask for the food
but, uh, I think the mother is enabler.

05:15.649 --> 05:19.251
<i>Amazing to me that her mother
had weight loss surgery herself,</i>

05:19.253 --> 05:23.188
<i>is continuing to help her
to eat as much as she wants,</i>

05:23.190 --> 05:26.792
and get her weight
up to 750 pounds.

05:26.794 --> 05:29.261
<i>So this is a very
pathological situation,</i>

05:29.263 --> 05:31.663
and I don't see any motivation.

05:31.665 --> 05:33.999
I don't see any goal
from Margaret.

05:34.001 --> 05:37.669
<i>But I'm ready to give her all the
tools she need to change her life</i>

05:37.671 --> 05:39.104
<i>and try to lose some weight.</i>

05:40.073 --> 05:44.042
Margaret, your BMI is 129.

05:44.044 --> 05:48.180
129 is very high BMI, okay?

05:48.182 --> 05:51.249
So this is very dangerous
situation you're in.

05:51.251 --> 05:53.118
So you have to change your life,

05:53.120 --> 05:56.121
and you have to try
harder, okay?

05:56.123 --> 05:59.224
While you're here, we can
control your eating habit.

05:59.226 --> 06:02.828
But when you go home,
you're gonna be on your own.

06:02.830 --> 06:05.697
And this is gonna be
the test for you.

06:05.699 --> 06:08.633
If you go home and you're not
able to change your eating habit,

06:08.635 --> 06:11.236
there's nothing
we can do for you, okay?

06:11.238 --> 06:13.972
So I'm gonna give you some
research that I want you to read.

06:13.974 --> 06:17.275
It will break down what
you can eat and cannot eat

06:17.277 --> 06:20.912
to do the diet
and what healthy eating is.

06:20.914 --> 06:25.484
So you need to follow it to where
you have some meaningful changes

06:25.486 --> 06:28.387
in your eating habit that's
gonna show on your scale.

06:28.389 --> 06:30.989
Okay? All right.

06:33.226 --> 06:36.695
Right now, we will get her
going in the right direction here

06:36.697 --> 06:38.730
<i>in a controlled environment.</i>

06:38.732 --> 06:42.701
But any progress we make
with her is going to be short-lived

06:42.703 --> 06:45.470
if she doesn't take
responsibility for her life.

06:45.472 --> 06:49.708
So what I want you to do is,
uh, every day, you read this.

06:49.710 --> 06:54.679
Three factor that control your weight,
your frequency, amount, and type of food.

06:54.681 --> 06:57.883
<i>But she doesn't have
any time for playing games.</i>

06:57.885 --> 07:01.086
<i>Because if she doesn't change
her situation soon,</i>

07:01.088 --> 07:02.754
then her time is gonna run out.

07:02.756 --> 07:06.591
This is gonna be something that you're
gonna have to work harder on, okay?

07:06.593 --> 07:09.227
- Okay.
- You think you can make all the changes?

07:09.229 --> 07:10.295
Yes.

07:10.297 --> 07:12.864
You think your mother
is gonna be on board1

07:12.866 --> 07:14.833
- with these changes?
- Yes.

07:14.835 --> 07:16.435
- So--
- She's on board.

07:16.437 --> 07:19.404
Okay. All right,
any questions?

07:22.341 --> 07:24.776
Just please help me.

07:24.778 --> 07:29.181
Well, we're gonna give you all the
tools you need, one step at a time.

07:29.183 --> 07:32.117
But you're gonna have
to do the hard work. Okay?

07:32.119 --> 07:34.453
I totally understand.

07:34.455 --> 07:39.324
Okay. Stick with healthy
eating habit and then try harder.

07:39.326 --> 07:41.793
And if you need anything,
give me a call.

07:41.795 --> 07:43.061
I will do, thank you.

07:43.063 --> 07:45.564
All right, I'll be back
and see you later, okay?

07:49.836 --> 07:51.870
<i>[Margaret] I'm thankful
I made it here.</i>

07:51.872 --> 07:53.605
<i>And that I've been able
to see Dr. Now.</i>

07:54.474 --> 07:56.975
<i>It's an answered prayer.</i>

07:56.977 --> 08:00.579
<i>Because I know I've let myself
get to a breaking point.</i>

08:01.848 --> 08:04.349
<i>And I could have easily
died especially when I fell.</i>

08:05.117 --> 08:07.085
<i>So I have to change now.</i>

08:07.087 --> 08:11.223
<i>Because if I don't, it's going
to be too late for me.</i>

08:25.171 --> 08:26.738
<i>[Margaret] I'm here
in the hospital.</i>

08:26.740 --> 08:28.540
<i>I've been here
for about two weeks,</i>

08:28.542 --> 08:32.244
<i>and that was not part of the
plan when I left the house.</i>

08:32.246 --> 08:37.315
<i>But Dr. Now said I might be able to go
home today, so I'm excited about that.</i>

08:38.217 --> 08:40.185
<i>I'm ready to get on
doing his program</i>

08:40.187 --> 08:41.920
<i>and showing him I can do it.</i>

08:41.922 --> 08:44.289
<i>I need his help
because things are bad,</i>

08:44.291 --> 08:46.124
<i>and they're just getting worse.</i>

08:48.227 --> 08:50.095
- Hey, you ready?
- [Margaret] Yes.

08:50.930 --> 08:53.098
- Ready to go home soon, baby?
- Yes.

08:54.400 --> 08:56.001
I'm ready to go home.

08:56.003 --> 08:57.235
[Millie] I'm just glad
to see you.

09:07.413 --> 09:08.413
[knocking at door]

09:08.981 --> 09:10.015
[Margaret] Who?

09:11.417 --> 09:12.951
Hello, how are you all doing?

09:12.953 --> 09:14.519
Hi, Doctor.

09:14.521 --> 09:15.954
Hi, Margaret, how are you doing?

09:15.956 --> 09:17.155
Doing pretty good.

09:17.157 --> 09:18.823
So how is your mom doing?

09:18.825 --> 09:20.325
You finally get
to meet me in person.

09:20.327 --> 09:22.127
All right, you doing okay?

09:22.129 --> 09:24.930
Yeah, working 42 hours
a week doesn't cut it.

09:24.932 --> 09:27.132
[laughs] I don't get to meet
very many people.

09:27.134 --> 09:30.035
Well, you know, Margaret
is in very poor shape.

09:30.037 --> 09:33.972
She came in at 750 pounds.

09:33.974 --> 09:36.241
- [Millie] That's the starting
point-- - And we kept her on a diet.

09:36.243 --> 09:39.344
In a few days,
she lost 30 pounds.

09:39.346 --> 09:43.081
- So that is what we need to continue at home.
- [Millie] We are.

09:43.083 --> 09:47.052
But I'm gonna give you a goal
of at least 30 pounds each month,

09:47.054 --> 09:49.854
when we wanna see you in
the office and get your weight.

09:49.856 --> 09:53.425
I expect that you lose
100 pounds in three months.

09:53.427 --> 09:54.793
- All right?
- In three months? Okay.

09:54.795 --> 09:58.163
Yeah. If you continue to lose
weight, then we can work with you

09:58.165 --> 10:00.165
and get you to a point
that you're gonna be able

10:00.167 --> 10:02.534
to hopefully have
weight loss surgery.

10:02.536 --> 10:04.135
[Millie] Margaret, how bad
do you want this surgery?

10:04.137 --> 10:05.303
[Margaret] Bad.

10:05.305 --> 10:07.839
- How bad do you want this surgery?
- Bad, Mama.

10:07.841 --> 10:09.941
Then we're gonna work
at every point to get it,

10:09.943 --> 10:11.376
- are we not?
- Yes.

10:11.378 --> 10:14.212
We will order physical therapy and
home health to come and see her.

10:14.214 --> 10:16.982
Get her stamina up so
she can get up and walk

10:16.984 --> 10:18.950
and perhaps come to the office.

10:18.952 --> 10:22.287
And home health is gonna help
with the personal hygiene.

10:22.289 --> 10:25.056
And we already had the
dietician come to talk to her.

10:25.058 --> 10:30.662
She has written the stuff that she need
to read every day and follow the diet.

10:30.664 --> 10:32.931
If she's not able to follow the
diet, we're not gonna be able

10:32.933 --> 10:35.834
- to do anything for her.
- We're going to follow this diet.

10:35.836 --> 10:39.037
No sugary drink
and a lot of exercise, okay?

10:39.039 --> 10:41.940
And you need to have
a positive influence on her.

10:41.942 --> 10:44.376
I had the gastric bypass
seven years ago.

10:44.378 --> 10:46.645
All right, so you should
know better, right?

10:46.647 --> 10:48.213
- You help her.
- Oh, I know all about that.

10:48.215 --> 10:51.116
No, it makes me have the heart
palpitations, the dumping syndrome.

10:51.118 --> 10:52.751
It makes me just
feel plain miserable.

10:52.753 --> 10:54.352
No, I know my limits.

10:54.354 --> 10:57.422
Okay. So we got
a lot of work to do.

10:57.424 --> 11:01.993
And now that you know in one week
we can lose 30 pounds in the hospital,

11:01.995 --> 11:04.729
you should be able
to do that at home too.

11:04.731 --> 11:07.332
- Is that not awesome?
- [Margaret] Yes, it is.

11:07.334 --> 11:10.268
We'll send her home today
and in a year and a half,

11:10.270 --> 11:12.971
- we can get her under 200.
- Yes.

11:12.973 --> 11:15.173
So this is gonna
be the goal, okay?

11:15.175 --> 11:18.209
I want her to be looking
like her mama.

11:18.211 --> 11:21.813
All right then. You're all looking
good and take care, okay?

11:21.815 --> 11:23.915
- I'll see you later.
- 'Cause you got some pretty eyes

11:23.917 --> 11:25.450
and you're a beautiful child.

11:28.120 --> 11:31.222
<i>[Dr. Now] We had Margaret in the
hospital for couple of weeks now.</i>

11:31.224 --> 11:34.693
<i>Most of the tests we ran
on her when she arrived</i>

11:34.695 --> 11:40.198
didn't show any immediate issues
with her except an infection in her leg

11:40.200 --> 11:43.034
<i>that cleared up
after we treated it.</i>

11:43.036 --> 11:47.272
While she's been here, we
had her on a controlled diet.

11:47.274 --> 11:51.042
<i>And in two weeks, we have
been able to get her weight down</i>

11:51.044 --> 11:53.778
67 pounds from when she arrived.

11:53.780 --> 11:58.183
<i>She was 752. Now she's at 685.</i>

11:58.185 --> 12:02.153
So we have made some progress
on that front with her.

12:02.155 --> 12:06.224
And we have also been
providing her physical therapy

12:06.226 --> 12:09.060
<i>to help her get up and walk.</i>

12:09.062 --> 12:12.263
<i>She pushed back some,
but overall she's doing well.</i>

12:12.265 --> 12:15.800
<i>And we have her moving
in the right direction now.</i>

12:15.802 --> 12:20.405
So the next step is for her to
show me she can do this on her own

12:20.407 --> 12:22.440
<i>if she wants to continue.</i>

12:22.442 --> 12:25.877
<i>Hopefully, Margaret
and her mom, Millie,</i>

12:25.879 --> 12:28.780
are as serious
as they are telling me.

12:28.782 --> 12:32.350
<i>Because they both need
to make a lot of changes</i>

12:32.352 --> 12:37.322
if Margaret is gonna have any
chance of success in the long term.

12:40.326 --> 12:43.194
I know it's rough,
but guess what?

12:43.196 --> 12:46.631
This is that miracle we
prayed for, isn't it? Mm-hmm?

12:47.933 --> 12:50.502
-[sobbing] -We finally
got it. Give me a high-five.

12:56.108 --> 13:00.178
- You prove to him you can do it.
- [crying]

13:00.180 --> 13:01.212
[Millie] Okay?

13:02.848 --> 13:04.649
You don't have to prove
to me, I already know it.

13:09.021 --> 13:12.724
- Prove him wrong.
- [crying]

13:12.726 --> 13:15.059
I'll put a picture
on the end of the bed

13:15.061 --> 13:17.962
and let you look at it every
day when you think about it.

13:17.964 --> 13:20.698
You say, "I'm gonna
prove them wrong."

13:42.054 --> 13:44.022
Oh, I need to put
some powder right here.

13:44.024 --> 13:45.924
You're rashed.

13:45.926 --> 13:48.860
<i>[Margaret] It's been a week since
I've come home from the hospital.</i>

13:48.862 --> 13:51.362
<i>And since then, I've been
trying to eat like Dr. Now says</i>

13:51.364 --> 13:53.898
<i>and to do the exercises
he wants.</i>

13:53.900 --> 13:58.069
<i>But ever since then, I've been
really scared of falling like I did before</i>

13:58.071 --> 14:01.372
<i>because my legs have such a
hard time supporting all my weight.</i>

14:03.142 --> 14:05.143
Look, look!
Isn't that something?

14:05.845 --> 14:08.012
Yes! Yes!

14:11.951 --> 14:14.152
<i>[Margaret] And I don't wanna
let her down,</i>

14:14.154 --> 14:17.021
<i>so I'm doing what
Dr. Now told us to do</i>

14:17.023 --> 14:19.123
<i>'cause I know I need
to get this surgery</i>

14:19.125 --> 14:21.392
<i>so I can live a life
more than this.</i>

14:25.130 --> 14:26.164
Ready, honey? You ready?

14:26.166 --> 14:27.532
One, two, three!

14:28.234 --> 14:29.400
Up, one more time.

14:32.071 --> 14:33.271
Now.

14:34.373 --> 14:37.041
- All right, you want a salad?
- Mm-hmm.

14:38.944 --> 14:41.512
<i>[Margaret] But food has always
been there for me.</i>

14:41.514 --> 14:43.648
<i>And if you take that
away from me,</i>

14:43.650 --> 14:46.150
<i>I'm not sure how
I'm supposed to get by.</i>

14:50.022 --> 14:52.090
<i>I've been eating
wrong my whole life.</i>

14:52.092 --> 14:55.793
<i>Not just the wrong foods
but for the wrong reasons too.</i>

14:55.795 --> 14:58.196
<i>In my kid years,
we were starving</i>

14:58.198 --> 15:00.031
<i>because my daddy
ate up all the food.</i>

15:00.033 --> 15:01.633
My dad was 1,000 pounds.

15:02.801 --> 15:05.470
<i>I have two other sisters,
Becky and Tiffany.</i>

15:05.472 --> 15:08.172
<i>And between us, all we
got to do is eat his leftovers.</i>

15:10.175 --> 15:14.345
<i>If we ever complained, Mama would
shush us so we wouldn't upset him</i>

15:14.347 --> 15:16.681
<i>because my dad
was a terrifying man.</i>

15:19.151 --> 15:22.487
[crying] My dad was
very controlling.

15:22.489 --> 15:26.157
<i>And if he said, "You be right
here," she had to be right there.</i>

15:26.159 --> 15:28.927
<i>That's how he was.</i>

15:28.929 --> 15:33.231
You'd wanna hide your feelings away
from him 'cause if you argued with him,

15:33.233 --> 15:38.503
then he would call us names
and just be very mean.

15:39.872 --> 15:41.372
<i>So I learned to sneak
into the kitchen</i>

15:41.374 --> 15:43.741
<i>and I ate his food
to get back at him.</i>

15:43.743 --> 15:46.210
<i>When I ate my dad's food
it was for revenge,</i>

15:46.212 --> 15:48.313
<i>so he wouldn't have it
for his self.</i>

15:48.315 --> 15:49.981
<i>[Millie] She'd get up
in the middle of the night.</i>

15:49.983 --> 15:52.050
If we had something leftover
in the ice box,

15:52.052 --> 15:54.652
she'd go in there
and she would make it

15:54.654 --> 15:56.688
look like she didn't eat it,
but she did eat it.

15:58.057 --> 16:01.693
<i>[Margaret] That's how I got to
120 pounds by the time I was 6.</i>

16:01.695 --> 16:06.564
<i>That's when I was diagnosed with early
signs of diabetes and an eating disorder.</i>

16:08.267 --> 16:11.970
<i>My mom, she started preparing
me my own special meals,</i>

16:11.972 --> 16:14.372
<i>just like she did for my dad.</i>

16:14.374 --> 16:16.074
<i>Except mine was healthier.</i>

16:16.076 --> 16:19.010
<i>And it worked,
I started to lose weight.</i>

16:19.012 --> 16:22.814
<i>And I was happier because I was getting
the attention and the love I was craving.</i>

16:22.816 --> 16:25.850
<i>But my dad did not like not
having all the attention on him.</i>

16:25.852 --> 16:30.154
<i>My dad would make my
mom leave us and go with him.</i>

16:30.156 --> 16:36.194
<i>[Millie] He demanded that I had to be at
the hospital with him every time he went.</i>

16:36.196 --> 16:38.029
<i>I had to go with him
to the doctor's.</i>

16:38.031 --> 16:40.298
<i>He had to go to Dallas.</i>

16:40.300 --> 16:45.003
And for two months, I had to
be completely away from my kids

16:45.005 --> 16:48.573
and live in Dallas, while
they stayed back in Arkansas.

16:50.142 --> 16:51.309
<i>[Margaret] My mom sent us
down the road</i>

16:51.311 --> 16:54.178
<i>to live with our grandmother
on my dad's side.</i>

16:54.180 --> 16:58.149
<i>She was the reason my dad
is as messed up as he was.</i>

16:58.151 --> 16:59.984
I'd call her "Evil Grandma."

17:00.652 --> 17:02.053
Or, "The Wicked Witch."

17:02.855 --> 17:05.690
<i>She's the reason why my dad
has so much hate in his heart.</i>

17:05.692 --> 17:08.960
<i>I remember one of the ways that
she would abuse me was with food.</i>

17:08.962 --> 17:13.765
<i>She made me eat 10 eggs in a
row 'cause I said I was hungry.</i>

17:13.767 --> 17:16.934
<i>But my mama must have figured
it out how my grandmother was,</i>

17:16.936 --> 17:19.504
<i>because she sent us to go stay
with my aunt Carla.</i>

17:19.506 --> 17:21.372
<i>Oh, Aunt Carla,
I really loved her.</i>

17:21.374 --> 17:23.374
<i>I really, really loved her.</i>

17:25.177 --> 17:26.811
<i>When we got to go
to Aunt Carla's,</i>

17:26.813 --> 17:28.913
<i>it was the first time
in my life where I could eat</i>

17:28.915 --> 17:31.449
<i>without being attacked
or ridiculed.</i>

17:31.451 --> 17:34.052
<i>The time we spent there were
the happiest times of my life.</i>

17:34.753 --> 17:36.354
<i>We got to be real close.</i>

17:36.356 --> 17:40.558
<i>And then, around when I started
high school, I lost my aunt Carla.</i>

17:42.428 --> 17:47.031
<i>She was like a second mama
to me, a guardian angel, my hero.</i>

17:47.033 --> 17:49.067
<i>She died very courageously</i>

17:49.069 --> 17:52.203
<i>from a blood-clot that broke off
from her heart and went to her lungs.</i>

17:52.205 --> 17:54.472
<i>Losing my aunt Carla
took a piece of my heart.</i>

17:54.474 --> 17:56.240
<i>I was crushed.</i>

17:56.242 --> 17:58.309
<i>So again, I resorted to food,</i>

17:58.311 --> 18:01.846
<i>because food was the only thing
I had to make the pain go away.</i>

18:01.848 --> 18:06.317
<i>And by the time I was 15,
I was pushing 300 pounds.</i>

18:06.319 --> 18:10.421
Everybody was cruel to Margaret
about one thing or the other.

18:10.423 --> 18:15.026
<i>By the time she was 16, she was so
depressed that she just wanted to die.</i>

18:15.028 --> 18:20.398
It was all due to her needing
to feed what was wrong in here.

18:21.066 --> 18:22.400
When she looked in the mirror,

18:22.634 --> 18:27.171
apparently she didn't love who
she was even though I loved her.

18:27.173 --> 18:31.342
<i>I don't know why she felt like
she wasn't important.</i>

18:31.344 --> 18:33.478
<i>I didn't know how to help her.</i>

18:35.047 --> 18:37.248
<i>[Margaret] I finished my
senior year without friends.</i>

18:37.250 --> 18:39.217
<i>And I just kept eating.</i>

18:39.219 --> 18:42.220
<i>So after I left high school,
I was about 400 pounds.</i>

18:43.956 --> 18:47.291
<i>I tried looking for a job
but nobody wanted me.</i>

18:47.293 --> 18:50.228
<i>By the time I was 20,
I was pushing 500 pounds.</i>

18:50.230 --> 18:53.097
<i>It was hard for me to drive
or do things for myself.</i>

18:53.866 --> 18:55.399
<i>I went on disability.</i>

18:56.034 --> 18:58.402
<i>My dad became more abusive.</i>

18:58.404 --> 19:01.272
<i>After that, my mom reached
a point of no return.</i>

19:01.274 --> 19:02.406
<i>So she packed her stuff</i>

19:02.408 --> 19:04.108
<i>and left
with my older sister, Tiffany,</i>

19:04.110 --> 19:05.810
<i>to take shelter with a friend.</i>

19:05.812 --> 19:09.881
<i>I woke up the next morning and
my sister and my mama were gone.</i>

19:09.883 --> 19:14.018
<i>So my dad told me she had abandoned
me because I was a fat pig and useless</i>

19:14.020 --> 19:15.953
<i>and she couldn't take care
of me no more.</i>

19:15.955 --> 19:20.424
Losing her was the most
upsetting part of my life.

19:20.426 --> 19:24.662
<i>I didn't care if I lived or
died, so I would eat to escape.</i>

19:24.664 --> 19:27.665
<i>I was so terribly lonely.</i>

19:27.667 --> 19:30.134
She would just sit there
and urinate on herself

19:30.136 --> 19:32.336
and that's pretty much
where she stayed.

19:32.338 --> 19:34.906
<i>I mean, she was always
a lonely child to begin with,</i>

19:34.908 --> 19:37.542
<i>and now she was
being alienated and thinking,</i>

19:37.544 --> 19:40.111
<i>"Mama don't love me,
she's abandoned me,"</i>

19:40.113 --> 19:42.246
then self-destruct.

19:44.016 --> 19:47.785
<i>[Margaret] I found out that my
dad told lies to my mama about me.</i>

19:47.787 --> 19:49.453
<i>He was telling her I hated her,</i>

19:49.455 --> 19:52.823
<i>and that I was furious
that she left without me,</i>

19:52.825 --> 19:54.992
<i>and that I was glad
she was gone.</i>

19:54.994 --> 19:58.462
<i>Hearing all of this for the first
time put me in a state of shock.</i>

19:58.464 --> 20:00.998
<i>I never wanted
to see my dad again.</i>

20:01.000 --> 20:03.234
<i>I begged my mom to take me back.</i>

20:03.236 --> 20:07.672
<i>[crying] Mama said, "Baby, you can
live with me, I never said you couldn't.</i>

20:07.674 --> 20:09.974
I never told you
I didn't want you.

20:09.976 --> 20:12.910
I just didn't want your daddy
no more."

20:12.912 --> 20:16.681
<i>I was so relieved, I kept
eating like I always did.</i>

20:16.683 --> 20:22.053
<i>And before I knew it, I was 750
pounds, dependent on my mama.</i>

20:22.055 --> 20:25.489
<i>My cellulitis infection
had gone into my blood stream.</i>

20:25.491 --> 20:29.493
<i>The infection kept getting worse,
and that took me down more.</i>

20:29.495 --> 20:33.564
<i>And before I knew it, I had
become dependent on my mama.</i>

20:35.300 --> 20:38.636
<i>But this feels like a stroke of
luck to be working with Dr. Now.</i>

20:38.638 --> 20:41.339
<i>I know he helps a lot
of people like me.</i>

20:41.341 --> 20:46.077
<i>And I have my daddy's voice in my
head telling me I'm a no good failure,</i>

20:46.079 --> 20:48.079
<i>and that just makes me
wanna give up.</i>

20:48.081 --> 20:50.081
<i>My biggest fear is
what if he's right.</i>

20:50.083 --> 20:52.149
<i>So I know I have to do this.</i>

20:52.151 --> 20:54.785
<i>I am just afraid that
I won't be able to.</i>

20:54.787 --> 20:56.988
<i>Because if I can't,
that's really the end for me.</i>

20:56.990 --> 20:58.756
<i>So I just gotta give it my best</i>

20:58.758 --> 21:00.958
<i>and hope and pray
that's good enough.</i>

21:17.409 --> 21:20.344
[Millie] All right, let me get
you up and let's get you going.

21:27.185 --> 21:28.185
You want some coffee?

21:28.187 --> 21:29.320
[Margaret] No.

21:29.788 --> 21:31.989
[Millie] One of them days?

21:31.991 --> 21:36.093
My mom woke me up this morning
and I hurt in the leg.

21:36.095 --> 21:37.695
All right,
get your bearings together.

21:37.697 --> 21:40.031
I'm gonna fix me a cup of coffee
and I be in here to get you up.

21:40.799 --> 21:42.533
[Margaret]
<i>Everyday is a new struggle.</i>

21:43.302 --> 21:45.903
<i>Today my leg
is really bad swollen.</i>

21:45.905 --> 21:48.172
And so it... It just...
It hurts.

21:48.174 --> 21:50.007
All right, Margaret.

21:50.009 --> 21:53.044
PT called me and they're
gonna be out this morning,

21:53.046 --> 21:55.012
but I need to get you up
before they come.

21:55.014 --> 21:56.781
Okay?

21:56.783 --> 21:58.949
So let's get this show
on the road.

21:58.951 --> 22:01.452
<i>Today, I'm supposed to go
to physical therapy,</i>

22:01.454 --> 22:04.255
<i>but usually I don't have
this swollen leg.</i>

22:04.257 --> 22:06.524
And so, I just didn't really
want to do nothing today.

22:11.363 --> 22:14.732
I did call and try to get her
on the schedule for next week,

22:14.734 --> 22:17.301
<i>and it's just been tough.
I mean, it's been tough.</i>

22:17.303 --> 22:20.471
<i>I can't tell you how many times
a week she tells me she quits.</i>

22:23.041 --> 22:25.309
[Millie] PT's gonna be in here.

22:26.078 --> 22:27.445
- [Margaret] Shut up!
- [dogs barking]

22:27.512 --> 22:30.481
[Millie] Dr. Now, he needs you
to get up 'cause of the blood clot.

22:30.483 --> 22:31.716
And every [bleep] damn
thing else.

22:31.718 --> 22:33.484
You already have a history
of diabetes.

22:33.486 --> 22:36.921
[Margaret] Yeah, I know. But they keep
pushing on you, and they keep pushing on me.

22:36.923 --> 22:38.989
[crying] I'm sick of it!

22:38.991 --> 22:40.591
- [dogs barking] - [Millie]
We're not coming today.

22:43.995 --> 22:45.396
[Margaret] Told you to just
leave me alone, Mom.

22:45.398 --> 22:47.098
[Millie] No, I'm not.

22:47.100 --> 22:49.100
[woman] I'm assuming
that was her mom.

22:49.102 --> 22:51.035
[Margaret] It's all about
what you want.

22:51.037 --> 22:53.137
[Millie] Okay, fine, I quit.
You want that?

22:53.271 --> 22:56.674
[Millie speaking]

22:58.143 --> 23:02.246
[woman] Okay, I don't know how quickly
we'll be able to get scheduled next week

23:02.248 --> 23:05.049
'cause we really moved
things around to see her.

23:05.051 --> 23:08.052
There's not any way
she'll do any PT today

23:08.054 --> 23:10.121
to make sure that she can get
scheduled for surgery?

23:14.926 --> 23:16.227
[Millie] Hello.

23:16.229 --> 23:18.696
Hi, Miss Margaret, I'm Mallory.

23:18.698 --> 23:20.464
So I'm the physical therapist.

23:20.466 --> 23:23.667
I think they just wanted us to
kind of do a general assessment

23:23.669 --> 23:25.870
and see kind of where you're at.

23:25.872 --> 23:28.172
Um, normally are you able
to, like...

23:28.174 --> 23:30.141
Right now, you're not...
I'm not gonna make you sit up.

23:30.143 --> 23:32.343
- But if you needed to sit up, are you able to sit up?
- Yes.

23:32.345 --> 23:33.677
- You're able to sit up all by yourself?
- Yes.

23:33.679 --> 23:35.679
- Not... No help, no nothing?
- No help.

23:35.681 --> 23:38.783
- Okay, what about like getting up from sitting to standing?
- I can get up like that, too.

23:38.785 --> 23:40.384
- You can?
- I can do it by myself.

23:40.386 --> 23:42.019
- Okay, you can do all that part by yourself?
- Yes.

23:42.021 --> 23:44.488
- No issues?
- It's just I'm having problems walking.

23:44.490 --> 23:47.124
- And so-- - Is it, like,
balance problems walking--

23:47.126 --> 23:48.325
- Yes.
- or pain problems?

23:48.327 --> 23:49.460
It's balance and pain.

23:49.462 --> 23:51.662
And pain. Okay, where is
the pain when you're walking?

23:51.664 --> 23:53.063
- My knees.
- In your knees.

23:53.065 --> 23:55.599
- Okay, is it the whole knee, or
like-- - Oh, yes. It's the whole knee.

23:55.601 --> 23:57.368
- Everywhere?
- Uh, they... I have no cartilage in them.

23:57.370 --> 23:59.203
- Okay, no cartilage in either knee.
- So they hurt.

23:59.205 --> 24:04.208
Okay, um, how far are you
normally able to walk

24:04.210 --> 24:06.811
before you have to sit?

24:06.813 --> 24:09.079
From here to the computer table.

24:09.081 --> 24:11.515
Okay, can you lift
this foot up toward you?

24:11.517 --> 24:13.417
Okay, hold it right there.
Don't let me push.

24:13.952 --> 24:14.985
- Does that hurt?
- Nope.

24:14.987 --> 24:16.587
No. Okay, can you push down
into my hand?

24:17.789 --> 24:19.457
Good what about this side?
Can you bring it up?

24:19.459 --> 24:21.592
Hold it up, don't let me push.

24:21.594 --> 24:23.227
- [Margaret groans]
- Ooh, that one hurt?

24:23.229 --> 24:25.896
- Or is it hard to do?
- It's hard to do it because it's making that knee hurt.

24:25.898 --> 24:27.698
[Mallory] That's making your knee
hurt when you try and hold it up?

24:27.700 --> 24:29.166
Okay, can you push down?

24:29.168 --> 24:30.167
- Does that make--
- Mm-mm.

24:30.169 --> 24:31.802
That makes
your knee hurt, too? Yeah?

24:31.804 --> 24:34.705
Here. Can you pull like
you're trying to pull me?

24:34.707 --> 24:37.641
Okay, what about push?
Can you push? Okay.

24:37.643 --> 24:40.077
Okay, can you hold your arm right
here? Don't let me push it down.

24:40.079 --> 24:42.179
Hold it right there.
Any pain? No?

24:42.181 --> 24:45.950
Can you lift it up above?
Yeah, you can? Okay.

24:45.952 --> 24:48.886
- All right, you have any weakness in your arms?
- No.

24:48.888 --> 24:51.789
Like, in your hands
or anything? No?

24:51.791 --> 24:54.859
We made you kind of a goody bag so
you have some stuff that you can do.

24:54.861 --> 24:56.260
'Cause I've got the purple one.

24:56.262 --> 24:58.162
Yeah, so this... This is blue.

24:58.164 --> 24:59.296
I don't know what...
They're just...

24:59.298 --> 25:01.632
- Different brands have
different colors-- - See?

25:02.334 --> 25:03.601
- Oh, yeah.
- But watch.

25:04.369 --> 25:05.503
I can...

25:06.071 --> 25:07.471
- Does that hurt?
- Nope.

25:07.473 --> 25:11.141
Okay, when you're standing, do
you have to hold on to something?

25:11.143 --> 25:12.409
- Yes.
- Yes? Okay.

25:12.411 --> 25:15.079
- If you don't hold on to
something-- - I'm wobbly.

25:15.081 --> 25:17.047
I just have to have
something to hold on to

25:17.049 --> 25:18.616
because I'm not
stable in the feet.

25:18.618 --> 25:20.084
Okay.

25:20.086 --> 25:22.119
- Okay, you have pain in your feet?
- No.

25:22.121 --> 25:24.288
-No, only in your knees? No hip pain?
-Nope.

25:24.290 --> 25:25.289
- No back pain?
- Mm-mm.

25:25.291 --> 25:27.324
Nothing? Okay.

25:27.326 --> 25:29.693
- We gave you a stress ball.
- [laughs]

25:29.695 --> 25:31.095
[Mallory laughs]
Girl, squeeze away.

25:31.097 --> 25:34.231
- You know how much I'm gonna be using this?
- [Mallory] That's okay.

25:34.233 --> 25:36.634
I can give you one of these
in each hand.

25:36.636 --> 25:39.169
<i>[Margaret] I feel better after
meeting the physical trainers.</i>

25:39.171 --> 25:42.339
<i>They're nice people and they
got my best interests at heart.</i>

25:42.341 --> 25:44.174
<i>So they can come back
on the right day</i>

25:44.176 --> 25:45.943
<i>and we can work together
some more.</i>

25:45.945 --> 25:48.379
<i>That will be good
when we do that.</i>

25:48.381 --> 25:52.182
<i>In the meantime, I'll do more
on my own and with my mama.</i>

25:52.184 --> 25:54.118
All right, it was good
working with you

25:54.120 --> 25:56.186
and we will, hopefully,
see you soon.

25:56.188 --> 25:57.922
- Okay, yes.
- Okay? All right.

25:57.924 --> 25:59.657
-Bye, nice to meet you.
-All right, yeah, you too. All right.

25:59.659 --> 26:01.125
- Thanks.
- No problem.

26:36.861 --> 26:39.296
[Millie] Margaret,
we have got to get up.

26:42.200 --> 26:44.335
- Come on.
- I'm coming, Mama.

26:44.337 --> 26:46.670
No, I don't have
a lot of time, Margaret.

26:48.673 --> 26:51.675
[bleeping].

26:51.677 --> 26:53.110
[Millie] Come on.

27:00.118 --> 27:01.485
[exhales]

27:19.204 --> 27:21.639
Push, push, push, push.

27:27.679 --> 27:29.546
It'll be worth it.

27:29.548 --> 27:32.082
Is this not what we've wanted
for seven years?

27:41.960 --> 27:44.194
You remember?
You were my partner then.

28:07.852 --> 28:09.420
[Millie] I know it's rough.

28:10.388 --> 28:11.655
[Margaret] Yeah,
you don't know nothing.

28:16.461 --> 28:17.661
[dog barking]

28:37.248 --> 28:38.415
I got you.

28:45.757 --> 28:47.925
I'm done.

28:47.927 --> 28:50.060
[Millie] I just want you to walk
one more time, and then back--

28:50.062 --> 28:51.462
I'm done.

28:51.464 --> 28:52.963
This is really hurting
me right now.

28:54.899 --> 28:57.935
Get over this "I feel sorry
for Margaret" stuff.

28:57.937 --> 29:00.104
- Mom, shut the hell up!
- [Millie] No, I'm not.

29:01.372 --> 29:04.575
It is very important
that he sees you're moving.

29:05.944 --> 29:08.345
I've let you get away
with this way too long.

29:09.180 --> 29:10.614
Now, it's time to get up.

29:11.983 --> 29:13.283
- [Margaret cries]
- Now, come on!

29:15.053 --> 29:17.888
- Why are you pushing me so--
- [Millie] Because I am.

29:17.890 --> 29:20.224
I'm gonna run
go get my clothes on.

29:27.232 --> 29:29.333
This is your last shot,
so come on.

29:29.701 --> 29:31.201
[sighs]

29:32.937 --> 29:35.672
[groaning]

29:35.674 --> 29:37.441
- Every step.
- [Margaret cries]

29:37.443 --> 29:39.276
[Millie] Yes, it will.
Every step.

30:17.182 --> 30:19.483
[Margaret] One, two.

30:29.427 --> 30:31.995
Now, because this leg
is so edematous,

30:31.997 --> 30:33.897
- scoot over some more in bed.
- I will.

30:33.899 --> 30:35.532
It's just swollen and it hurts.

30:36.334 --> 30:37.434
I'm getting sick.

30:38.036 --> 30:39.203
That's that shot.

30:40.371 --> 30:42.606
[groaning]

30:42.907 --> 30:44.341
Oh.

31:06.130 --> 31:08.765
<i>[Margaret] I've been working
really hard this past month.</i>

31:08.767 --> 31:13.370
<i>And I've worked out a lot
and got a lot more mobile.</i>

31:13.372 --> 31:18.175
<i>But I've had to do it all on my own
because PT has not been coming.</i>

31:19.143 --> 31:21.278
<i>But I've been doing fine
on my own.</i>

31:22.146 --> 31:23.881
<i>I got a little bit more slower,</i>

31:23.883 --> 31:26.183
<i>and maybe the PT
won't like that.</i>

31:28.453 --> 31:32.322
<i>But it's better to me that way
because my leg has been hurting me.</i>

31:33.091 --> 31:35.158
<i>And it keeps getting worse.</i>

31:36.160 --> 31:39.830
<i>I don't wanna push myself
so far that I injure myself.</i>

31:39.832 --> 31:44.167
<i>But I've been able to get a lot more
mobile and that feels really good.</i>

31:45.336 --> 31:48.105
<i>I'm really happy about that.</i>

31:48.107 --> 31:51.074
<i>And I really want Dr. Now to
see how much weight I've lost,</i>

31:51.910 --> 31:54.645
<i>and how much I can get around.</i>

31:54.647 --> 32:00.050
<i>But my mom had to work today, so
she can't drive me to my appointment.</i>

32:00.052 --> 32:04.054
<i>So I'm not going to the clinic
because I had to cancel it.</i>

32:04.056 --> 32:07.591
<i>But Dr. Now set up a video
call to see me anyways.</i>

32:10.261 --> 32:13.497
<i>And I'm worried that he's gonna
say I'm not taking it seriously.</i>

32:14.098 --> 32:17.034
<i>But I really am.</i>

32:17.036 --> 32:22.272
<i>If it wasn't for my leg hurting so
much, then I'd be doing even more.</i>

32:22.274 --> 32:24.341
<i>It's just really that
my mama's gotta work.</i>

32:28.980 --> 32:31.114
[video call rings]

32:33.284 --> 32:34.384
<i>Hi, Margaret.</i>

