47:19.169 --> 47:21.204
<i>I've worked so hard
and it feels so long</i>

47:21.206 --> 47:24.073
<i>that I really think
it's gonna happen today.</i>

47:24.075 --> 47:28.377
<i>The last time I was here,
I weighed 632 pounds.</i>

47:28.379 --> 47:31.080
<i>If I was still losing
at a steady pace,</i>

47:31.082 --> 47:33.850
<i>I would have lost
another 50 pounds this month.</i>

47:33.852 --> 47:36.285
<i>That means I would have
been down to the 500's.</i>

47:36.287 --> 47:38.387
<i>And I really hope
I made it there.</i>

47:38.389 --> 47:42.024
[Millie] And we'll find out what we
are today, I hope we're in the 5's.

47:42.392 --> 47:43.559
Wouldn't that be cool?

47:44.728 --> 47:46.229
Wouldn't that be cool?

47:47.364 --> 47:50.166
But even if we're in the
low six, we don't care.

47:52.569 --> 47:54.103
But I'm betting we are.

47:55.339 --> 47:56.272
Margaret.

47:56.874 --> 47:58.007
All right.

48:09.186 --> 48:12.088
- Oh, don't dump me out!
- I'm not gonna dump you out.

48:12.090 --> 48:14.523
- I just got you through the door.
- All right.

48:17.995 --> 48:19.695
Just got to give me a second.

48:21.965 --> 48:24.367
[Millie] Once you get up there
you gotta let go.

48:24.369 --> 48:28.504
[sighing in exhaustion] Come on,
hurry, calculate. Hurry, hurry, hurry.

48:32.042 --> 48:33.509
Come on, come on, come on.

48:37.514 --> 48:39.482
Your weight is 626.

48:40.250 --> 48:41.617
I didn't lose enough.

48:42.486 --> 48:44.987
Well, we're still doing good.

48:44.989 --> 48:46.022
It's fine.

48:46.024 --> 48:48.758
[panting]

48:48.760 --> 48:51.294
<i>[Margaret] I don't know what
happened or how that's right.</i>

48:56.466 --> 48:59.168
<i>I just hope Dr. Now
can be happy with what I did.</i>

48:59.403 --> 49:00.670
[Millie] I'm going.

49:00.672 --> 49:03.072
<i>[Margaret] And that
he'll see that.</i>

49:03.074 --> 49:06.042
<i>And he'll go ahead and schedule
me for weight loss surgery.</i>

49:10.113 --> 49:12.214
<i>I think I'm just having
a bad day.</i>

49:14.117 --> 49:15.885
How about that?

49:15.887 --> 49:17.486
<i>[Margaret] I'm all swolled up.</i>

49:21.224 --> 49:22.425
[knocking at door]

49:25.796 --> 49:27.363
Hello, how y'all doing?

49:27.365 --> 49:29.065
- [Millie] Okay.
- Doing pretty good.

49:29.067 --> 49:30.032
Good.

49:30.434 --> 49:31.367
Well,

49:32.269 --> 49:34.971
Margaret how's everything
going with you?

49:34.973 --> 49:36.806
I'm disappointed.

49:36.808 --> 49:40.776
Well, uh, what do you mean
you're disappointed?

49:40.778 --> 49:43.312
Cause I thought I would lose
more than what I've lost.

49:43.314 --> 49:47.249
Well, if you were
doing your part,

49:47.251 --> 49:50.019
you would have lost 50 pounds
this past month.

49:50.021 --> 49:52.288
So, it looks like you backslid.

49:52.290 --> 49:55.524
And you're still not
fully cooperating with PT.

49:55.526 --> 49:58.260
And you refused
to do psychotherapy.

49:58.262 --> 50:00.196
So, this isn't good.

50:00.198 --> 50:03.466
Because you're still 626 pounds.

50:03.468 --> 50:08.371
Your BMI today is 107.5.

50:08.373 --> 50:14.343
So, you basically, both of you,
went back to your old habits.

50:14.345 --> 50:16.312
We don't know what we did wrong.

50:16.314 --> 50:19.081
She's still eating the same way.

50:20.183 --> 50:23.119
- I mean yesterday-- - Okay,
hold on right there. Okay?

50:23.121 --> 50:25.121
- Overeating--
- [Dr. Now] Just hold on.

50:25.123 --> 50:27.156
And, like, you don't know
what is going on?

50:27.158 --> 50:30.159
There's a simple, simple math.

50:30.161 --> 50:33.029
You're eating too much,
you're not gonna lose weight.

50:33.031 --> 50:35.164
Which part of this
is very hard to understand?

50:35.166 --> 50:40.036
That she's eating at least four times
as much as what she should be eating.

50:42.239 --> 50:46.142
So, why we overeating and playing
like we don't know what's going on?

50:46.144 --> 50:48.978
But she didn't overeat.

50:48.980 --> 50:51.347
- She's still eating the same-- -
You want to argue that with the scale?

50:51.349 --> 50:53.215
Don't argue with me.

50:53.217 --> 50:55.051
- But she didn't overeat.
- You argue that with the scale.

50:55.053 --> 50:58.320
She couldn't overeat
I gave her proportioned meals.

50:58.322 --> 51:01.057
And it's the same
as I've always given her.

51:01.059 --> 51:05.061
The only thing that we know
that might have been different

51:05.063 --> 51:10.099
is she quit eating the vinaigrette
and ate honey mustard dressing.

51:10.101 --> 51:13.269
Is she eat, what,
a gallon of honey mustard?

51:13.271 --> 51:16.038
Now, I don't know how much
she put on her salad.

51:16.040 --> 51:20.342
- [Margaret] The two cups.
- But I can tell you that's the only difference.

51:20.344 --> 51:22.978
So she's gaining
from thin air, right?

51:22.980 --> 51:24.880
[Millie] Well, I don't know
how she done it.

51:24.882 --> 51:26.048
This is what I know.

51:26.050 --> 51:27.883
Now, I'm the one
who fixes her meals.

51:27.885 --> 51:31.153
- And unless she's getting up when I'm not there.
- No.

51:31.155 --> 51:34.023
I'm not getting up
and I promise you that.

51:34.025 --> 51:37.393
I don't know what
went wrong, I don't know.

51:37.395 --> 51:40.463
- Did you quit exercising during the day?
- No.

51:42.866 --> 51:46.669
For her to be 600 pounds
and keep that 600 pounds,

51:46.671 --> 51:49.605
she's eating
5,000-6,000 calories a day.

51:50.207 --> 51:54.143
If she eat a 1,000
or 1,200 calorie

51:54.145 --> 51:56.345
she gonna lose 100 pounds
in one month.

51:56.813 --> 51:58.314
Okay?

51:58.316 --> 52:00.549
And don't come and tell me
what you're eating.

52:00.551 --> 52:03.752
You want to argue all that
with the scale? Be my guest.

52:03.754 --> 52:04.853
Okay?

52:04.855 --> 52:07.590
If she's not losing weight,
she's eating too much.

52:07.592 --> 52:11.660
You know, she's eating the food that
belongs next five years ahead of time.

52:13.830 --> 52:17.032
Unless you drink your shake in the
morning and you drink a shake at night,

52:17.034 --> 52:19.201
and that's only
300 calories a day.

52:19.203 --> 52:22.571
Who said she should
be drinking a shake?

52:22.573 --> 52:24.673
You are the enabler
in that house.

52:24.675 --> 52:27.343
- You are telling her something that is not correct.
- [Millie] A protein shake.

52:27.345 --> 52:29.111
Well, who said protein shake

52:29.113 --> 52:31.814
- was okay to drink?
- [Millie] Nobody.

52:31.816 --> 52:35.251
So between you two, whatever
is going on, we're killing her.

52:35.253 --> 52:39.889
And if you don't go to therapy and do
what you need, and take this seriously,

52:39.891 --> 52:44.160
my bet is you come in next month
you probably gain some weight.

52:44.162 --> 52:47.863
- [Millie] We didn't even do a month before we came here.
- And give me the same story

52:47.865 --> 52:49.665
that you're not eating
very much,

52:49.667 --> 52:55.237
and between you two, you know, was
maybe honey mustard, and, you know.

52:55.239 --> 52:56.906
I don't want to hear excuses.

52:56.908 --> 52:58.374
I don't want to see the tears.

52:58.376 --> 53:01.744
I don't want to see
any drama in here.

53:01.746 --> 53:03.946
That we don't know
what's going on

53:03.948 --> 53:07.349
and all these stories
that none of it is believable.

53:08.018 --> 53:10.219
So, from here it is simple.

53:10.221 --> 53:13.389
I want you to lose 35 pounds
by next month.

53:13.391 --> 53:15.891
And start seeing psychotherapy.

53:15.893 --> 53:20.963
If not, then we are not
moving ahead with you.

53:20.965 --> 53:24.333
Just because we did not lose it
Margaret, does not mean we can't--

53:24.335 --> 53:26.635
I want to go home.

53:30.073 --> 53:33.475
That's all I want. I just want
out of this office and go home.

53:40.984 --> 53:43.652
Try harder.
You can do it.

53:44.387 --> 53:46.088
Like you're mom said.

53:46.155 --> 53:47.089
Okay?

53:47.156 --> 53:50.059
We have faith that
you can do this, Margaret.

53:50.061 --> 53:54.330
- We're not quitting.
- And you quit, you're never gonna make it.

53:54.332 --> 53:55.965
Okay?

53:55.967 --> 53:59.001
We're gonna get on this horse and
we're gonna do what Dr. Now says.

53:59.003 --> 54:03.739
All right, if you need
anything, give me a call.

54:03.741 --> 54:05.374
- Sure will.
- All right.

54:09.613 --> 54:11.847
<i>[Dr. Now] I'm obviously
disappointed</i>

54:11.849 --> 54:16.185
<i>from what I see from Margaret
and Millie's choices this past month.</i>

54:16.187 --> 54:21.156
There are elements where
Millie tells Margaret positive things.

54:21.158 --> 54:24.660
<i>And pushes her to keep going
and not quit.</i>

54:24.662 --> 54:26.295
<i>But those are all cliches.</i>

54:26.297 --> 54:28.197
<i>What matters is action.</i>

54:28.199 --> 54:33.669
And it is very dangerous when you have
a dynamic where someone talk's the talk,

54:33.671 --> 54:37.973
<i>but doesn't support it with
any of the choices they make.</i>

54:37.975 --> 54:42.645
I have no doubt that Millie loves
Margaret and wants the best for her.

54:42.647 --> 54:46.815
<i>She talks supporting then
contradicts that with her actions.</i>

54:46.817 --> 54:50.085
<i>So whatever progress they have
will be short-lived.</i>

54:50.087 --> 54:52.821
<i>And unless they both
start that process,</i>

54:52.823 --> 54:55.324
<i>we won't be moving ahead
with Margaret.</i>

54:56.092 --> 54:57.960
[Margaret]
<i>I was disappointed.</i>

54:59.029 --> 55:00.296
<i>Let down.</i>

55:02.232 --> 55:04.333
<i>Because I thought I did better
than what I did.</i>

55:05.268 --> 55:09.204
<i>I'm angry at myself
cause I could have did better.</i>

55:09.206 --> 55:12.341
<i>Just disappointed.
[heavy sigh]</i>

55:13.576 --> 55:15.311
<i>But don't give up.</i>

55:17.347 --> 55:20.082
<i>You'll have your
disappointments, but don't give up.</i>

55:40.904 --> 55:43.605
Here, wash your face down.

55:44.140 --> 55:46.475
Make ya feel better.
Get you started.

55:48.144 --> 55:51.013
<i>[Margaret] It's been a week
since my appointment with Dr. Now.</i>

55:51.015 --> 55:53.148
<i>Since then,
me and my mom has talked,</i>

55:53.150 --> 55:58.153
<i>and decided that surgery is the most
important thing that could happen in my life.</i>

55:58.155 --> 56:00.189
- Through with the wash rag?
- Yeah, I just threw it there.

56:00.191 --> 56:01.690
Okay.

56:01.692 --> 56:04.193
<i>[Margaret] So we told Dr. Now
we would do therapy.</i>

56:07.097 --> 56:08.297
- [knocking at door]
- [dogs barking]

56:09.366 --> 56:12.301
All right, get back.

56:14.204 --> 56:16.905
- [Paradise] Hi there, I'm Dr. Paradise.
- Hello.

56:16.907 --> 56:19.041
- I'm Millie, I'm Margaret's mom.
- [Paradise] Hi, Millie.

56:19.043 --> 56:21.176
Would you like to sit
over here where she's at?

56:22.112 --> 56:24.546
[Paradise] You have a
lot of protectors, don't you?

56:24.548 --> 56:26.515
- [Margaret] Yes, sir.
- [Millie] All right!

56:26.517 --> 56:28.283
All right, enough!

56:30.086 --> 56:31.286
Enough!

56:32.655 --> 56:34.390
They don't bite.
They're all friendly.

56:34.392 --> 56:36.425
- I'm Millie and this is Margaret.
- Millie and Margaret, okay.

56:36.427 --> 56:39.461
-I'm Mom.
-Good. Hi, Mom. Good to meet you.

56:39.463 --> 56:41.964
So, Margaret,
I'm glad to see you.

56:41.966 --> 56:44.566
Um, thanks for having me
in your house.

56:44.568 --> 56:47.102
Tell me about growing up in
your house. What was it like?

56:48.271 --> 56:49.471
Hell.

56:52.842 --> 56:55.110
You're getting sad pretty
quick talking about that.

56:55.845 --> 56:56.578
[Millie] We got this.

56:57.881 --> 56:58.580
Give me your hand.

57:00.016 --> 57:01.283
We got this.

57:01.285 --> 57:03.285
We've got to heal now,
do we not?

57:04.487 --> 57:07.956
So you had a tough childhood.

57:07.958 --> 57:10.526
So tough that you
can't even talk about it.

57:11.127 --> 57:13.061
When did you start getting big?

57:15.031 --> 57:18.400
[Millie] She was about...
In kindergarten she was big.

57:18.402 --> 57:20.068
I was bullied.

57:20.870 --> 57:22.638
Okay. Who protected you?

57:23.373 --> 57:25.474
I didn't have anybody
to protect me.

57:26.709 --> 57:29.144
You know, I get the sense
that your mom protects you,

57:29.146 --> 57:32.915
even in just a couple minutes
talking together,

57:32.917 --> 57:34.917
your mom steps in
and says stuff.

57:34.919 --> 57:36.685
She wasn't there.

57:36.687 --> 57:38.187
- What do you--
- [Millie] I had to work.

57:38.189 --> 57:40.923
Did you work all the way
through her growing up?

57:40.925 --> 57:41.990
- [Millie] Yes. I still work.
- Okay.

57:41.992 --> 57:43.926
- You still work now.
- Yes.

57:43.928 --> 57:46.028
What is... Margaret's
by herself during the day?

57:46.030 --> 57:48.096
- Yes.
- [Millie] Okay.

57:48.098 --> 57:51.033
Um, how do you do when
you're by yourself, Margaret?

57:51.035 --> 57:53.802
I talk to her on the phone
while she's a work.

57:53.804 --> 57:55.971
So you talk to each other
all day on the phone?

57:55.973 --> 58:00.275
[Millie] Yes, we may have a
seven-eight hour [laughs] phone call.

58:00.277 --> 58:03.278
- It sounds like you were a very active mother.
- [Millie] Yes.

58:03.280 --> 58:05.447
- My babies are my world.
- [Paradise] Right.

58:06.082 --> 58:07.149
She's not a baby.

58:07.383 --> 58:08.383
She's my baby.

58:08.385 --> 58:10.252
She's your baby and she's 35.

58:10.254 --> 58:13.922
She's still my baby.
She'll always be my baby.

58:13.924 --> 58:17.159
You know, the word "baby"
implies a lot of care.

58:18.027 --> 58:20.095
She's my baby,
she's the youngest.

58:20.097 --> 58:22.331
[Paradise] I'm a little
worried... So yeah, I...

58:22.333 --> 58:25.100
You know, I don't know you very
well Margaret, we just started talking.

58:25.102 --> 58:30.038
But I think that's gonna be my theme
with you, is making you not a baby.

58:30.040 --> 58:33.876
I think you must believe that
the world is a dangerous place.

58:33.878 --> 58:36.979
- It is, and I'm scared-- -
[Millie] We don't trust nobody.

58:36.981 --> 58:38.881
- [Dr. Paradise] And that,
and that-- - I don't let nobody in.

58:38.883 --> 58:40.315
And that people
will hurt you, right?

58:40.317 --> 58:41.750
They'll hurt me.

58:41.752 --> 58:43.752
- That's the thing.
- [Millie] And we have a trust issue.

58:43.754 --> 58:45.954
- I have to say, cause I'm there too.
- I have trust issues.

58:45.956 --> 58:50.993
That's why I become her
comfort zone. Her security blanket.

58:50.995 --> 58:52.461
And I know
you've been doing it forever.

58:52.463 --> 58:56.298
But I'm gonna push you guys to
be a little bit more independent.

58:56.900 --> 58:57.866
- And, and--
- All right.

58:57.868 --> 58:59.167
[Margaret] How do you do that?

58:59.169 --> 59:00.635
You practice.

59:00.637 --> 59:04.406
I want you guys to practice more and
more times of independence for her.

59:04.408 --> 59:06.308
And you get to step back.

59:06.310 --> 59:08.677
And you get to
attend to your job,

59:08.679 --> 59:11.880
and your relationships, and you're
always gonna be there for her.

59:11.882 --> 59:15.050
But you're gonna be there
for her in a way that's healthy

59:15.052 --> 59:17.886
and appropriate
for a 35-year-old woman.

59:17.888 --> 59:20.656
[Margaret] So more or less you're saying
[voice breaks] that I don't need her.

59:20.658 --> 59:21.857
- No.
- [Millie] No, Margaret.

59:21.859 --> 59:24.092
He's not saying
that you don't need me.

59:24.094 --> 59:27.296
- He's more of less saying that my comfort zone is gone.
- He's saying...

59:27.298 --> 59:29.097
Margaret, you will always--

59:29.099 --> 59:30.799
[Margaret] I need to let go
of my comfort zone.

59:30.801 --> 59:32.801
[Millie] He's not saying
you need to let go of me.

59:32.803 --> 59:36.171
Let's take the food from her,
so that's a comfort zone gone.

59:36.173 --> 59:38.240
Okay, now let's take
the mother away from her,

59:38.242 --> 59:40.008
that's another
comfort zone gone.

59:40.010 --> 59:41.209
Maybe we'll just
keep breaking her,

59:41.211 --> 59:42.878
- and breaking her, and breaking her.
- [Mille] Margaret.

59:42.880 --> 59:45.013
Margaret, your mother
can be very present.

59:45.015 --> 59:46.682
I'm just, I'm done.
[crying]

59:46.684 --> 59:49.251
-I'm done, I'm done, I'm done.
-[Millie] We're a team. We're a team.

59:49.253 --> 59:52.421
I'm always gonna love you.
Give me a team.

59:52.423 --> 59:56.858
Millie, Millie, do you notice in
this moment that you're jumping in?

59:56.860 --> 1:00:00.796
Because I know how stressful
she is and it is a meltdown.

1:00:00.798 --> 1:00:03.765
And she will
want to resort to food.

1:00:03.767 --> 1:00:08.003
And here's an opportunity,
even in this little tiny moment.

1:00:08.005 --> 1:00:09.438
We're gonna let her
have her feelings,

1:00:09.440 --> 1:00:12.107
'cause I think she's capable
of working through this.

1:00:12.109 --> 1:00:14.209
[yelling] You don't know me!

1:00:14.211 --> 1:00:16.244
[crying continues]

1:00:16.246 --> 1:00:18.113
See the resistance?

1:00:18.115 --> 1:00:21.883
Just get out of my house, just
go, just go, get out of my house.

1:00:21.885 --> 1:00:24.186
I'm done.

1:00:24.188 --> 1:00:27.656
-He's not saying Margaret that I'm
abandoning you -I'm done. I'm done.

1:00:27.658 --> 1:00:30.959
It's interesting she's
getting up in response to this.

1:00:32.962 --> 1:00:37.165
Isn't it neat that she's getting
out of bed in response to this?

1:00:37.167 --> 1:00:39.368
But I want you to notice
the urge, right now,

1:00:39.370 --> 1:00:41.436
that you have to jump in
and comfort her.

1:00:41.438 --> 1:00:42.838
- And I--
- That's my job.

1:00:42.840 --> 1:00:45.240
I think of her
as a grown up adult.

1:00:45.242 --> 1:00:48.977
And we've gotta
let her self soothe.

1:00:48.979 --> 1:00:51.079
Work on this on her own, in
order for her to realize that.

1:00:51.081 --> 1:00:55.717
The solution is to, um...
to watch her

1:00:55.719 --> 1:00:57.953
- take care of herself.
- [Millie] Margaret, do you want your walker?

1:00:57.955 --> 1:01:01.056
Margaret, please, do not
try to walk without nothing.

1:01:03.126 --> 1:01:04.559
She's trying to get away
from y'all.

1:01:04.561 --> 1:01:06.161
Okay.

1:01:06.163 --> 1:01:09.898
But again, I want you to watch she's
doing this without anybody's help.

1:01:09.900 --> 1:01:13.301
I want her to go in and feel
her feelings and be okay.

1:01:13.303 --> 1:01:15.937
She's a grown up. She's
gonna go deal with her feelings.

1:01:15.939 --> 1:01:17.406
She's gonna come out
in a couple hours

1:01:17.408 --> 1:01:20.342
and I'm sure you guys will
have a fine time after that.

1:01:20.344 --> 1:01:21.977
And I think this is really good.

1:01:21.979 --> 1:01:23.211
This is the push
and pull, right?

1:01:23.213 --> 1:01:26.648
You may see that as really
negative, I'm proud of her.

1:01:26.650 --> 1:01:28.950
- She basically said--
- I'm proud of her, in a way.

1:01:28.952 --> 1:01:30.919
But I've seen the setbacks.

1:01:30.921 --> 1:01:32.354
I don't think
this is a setback at all,

1:01:32.356 --> 1:01:33.355
I think this is a breakthrough.

1:01:33.357 --> 1:01:35.557
She just stuck up for herself.

1:01:35.559 --> 1:01:38.527
Somebody pushing her
and she got space from it.

